  "description": "<i>Mortality Bytes</i> casts players again in the role of Rincewind, from <a href=\"https://www.mobygames.com/search/quick?game=Discworld+1\">the first game</a>.<br><br>Death, the grim reaper, who normally ushers the Discworld inhabitants into the afterlife, is on an extended vacation. This means that those whose &quot;time is up&quot; are faltering around in limbo. Now it's up to Rincewind to bring him back or suffer the fate of immortality.<br><br>Gameplay is divided into 4 Acts. There are many locations to explore and a multitude of obstacles in Rincewind's path to overcome. Conversations with characters and interaction with inventory objects is necessary to move ahead.<br><br>The game features unique humour similar to the previous game.",
